DENGUE/DHF - CUBA (13)
**********************
A ProMED-mail post
See Also
Dengue/DHF - Cuba (11) 971112114156
Dengue/DHF - Cuba (12) (not yet archived)
Date: Sun, 12 Apr 1998 17:52:48 -0700
From: Steve Berger <mberger@post.tau.ac.il>

The following background data on dengue in Cuba were extracted from the
GIDEON software program:
- No cases of dengue were reported from Cuba during 1945 to 1977.
- More than 500,000 cases (158 fatal) were reported during an epidemic in
1977-1981.
Nationwide seroprevalence rates increased from 2.6% prior to 1977, to 44.6%
in 1978.
Dengue hemorrhagic fever (DHF) was first reported in 1981. 10,312 cases of
DHF (158 fatal) were reported during 1981 to 1996.
- 477,440 cases of dengue were reported in 1977; 75,692 in 1978; 1,497 in
1979; 169 in 1980.
- 344,203 cases (3% of the population) were reported in 1981 - 10,312 of
these were characterized as dengue hemorrhagic fever (158 fatal).
- No cases of dengue were reported during 1988 to 1992. 2,946 cases (205
DHF, 12 fatal) were reported from Santiago de Cuba during January to July
1997.
